org.apache.hadoop.hive.registry

Interface ServiceInstanceSet<InstanceType extends ServiceInstance>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    HiveServer2HAInstanceSet, LlapServiceInstanceSet
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HS2ActivePassiveHARegistry

    public interface ServiceInstanceSet<InstanceType extends ServiceInstance>
    Note: For most of the implementations, there's no guarantee that the ServiceInstance returned by one invocation is the same as the instance returned by another invocation. e.g. the ZK registry returns a new ServiceInstance object each time a getInstance call is made.

    • Method Detail

      • getAll

        Collection<InstanceType> getAll()
        Get an instance mapping which map worker identity to each instance. The worker identity does not collide between restarts, so each restart will have a unique id, while having the same host/ip pair.
        Returns:
        instance list

      • getInstance

        InstanceType getInstance(String name)
        Get an instance by worker identity.
        Parameters:
        name - worker id
        Returns:
        instance

      • getByHost

        Set<InstanceType> getByHost(String host)
        Get a list of service instances for a given host. The list could include dead and alive instances.
        Parameters:
        host - hostname
        Returns:
        instance list

      • size

        int size()
        Get number of instances in the currently available.
        Returns:
        - number of instances
